Class Node.Builder

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.gef.graph.Node.Builder
Enclosing class:
Node
public static class Node.Builder extends Object
The Node.Builder can be used to construct a Node little by little.

  • Constructor Summary

    Constructors
    Constructor
    Description
    Builder()
    Constructs a new (anonymous) context-free Node.Builder, which can only be used to construct a single node via buildNode(), i.e. which cannot be chained.
    Builder(Graph.Builder.Context context)
    Constructs a new (anonymous) Node.Builder for the given Graph.Builder.Context.
    Builder(Graph.Builder.Context context, Object key)
    Constructs a new identifiable Node.Builder for the given Graph.Builder.Context.
